.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 884<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/10/02 11:31:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Introduction to Roleplaying</span><hr size=1> The thing of it is... if you are -thinking- something and you don't want anyone to react to it, don't emote it.  If it is something that you might want someone to infer from your expression, well.. give them the expression from which they are going to infer it.<br>
